## What this commit does
Binds the 9 previously-unbound TraceServerInterface methods. Key finding:
RemoteHTTPTraceServer inherits the Protocol, so an unbound method silently
returns None (Protocol `...` body) instead of raising — completeness is a
correctness fix, not cosmetics. Verified all 115 Protocol methods are now
genuinely defined (none inherited-stub-only).
- 6 agent methods: genai_otel_export (NotImplementedError stub, protobuf
  ingest, mirrors otel_export), agent_agents_query (/agents/query),
  agent_versions_query (/agents/agent-versions/query), agent_search
  (/agents/search), agent_traces_chat (/agents/traces/chat),
  agent_conversation_chat (/agents/conversations/chat).
- 3 non-agent: call_stats (/calls/stats), calls_score (/calls/score),
  eval_results_query (/v2/{entity}/{project}/eval_results/query).

## Hints for Future Agents
- eval_results_query is the only non-trivial binding: its core route
  (object_router) takes entity/project from the PATH and a project-LESS body
  (EvalResultsQueryBody). Both EvalResultsQueryReq and ...Body are strict
  (extra=forbid), so you MUST strip project_id: post
  EvalResultsQueryBody(**req.model_dump(exclude={'project_id'})) — posting the
  full Req 422s on the extra project_id field.
- genai_otel_export is a deliberate NotImplementedError: the route
  (/agents/otel/v1/traces) is protobuf and clients ingest server-side via the
  OTel path, not through this binding (same stance as otel_export).
- Tests mock the weave.utils.http_requests.post boundary and assert
  route + parsed response; genai_otel_export test asserts NotImplementedError.
- Live-verified the read path against megatruong/codex-test1 on
  trace.wandb.ai before relocating: get_agent_spans + filter + to_pandas work.

